The `isPrime` function is a simple implementation of the trial division method to check if a number is prime. It returns `false` if the number is less than 2 (since 2 is the smallest prime number) or if any integer from 2 to the square root of the number divides it evenly. If none of these conditions are met, the function returns `true`, indicating that the number is prime.

